      "role": "user",
      "content": "makes sense. but wouldn't critics say that the \"more speech\" argument is kind of naive or even dangerous in the digital age? like, if the internet is flooded with bots or coordinated disinformation, the \"marketplace\" basically breaks. how would a philosopher respond to the idea that this approach is just unrealistic and lets bad actors win?",
